<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1378,1604]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1378,1404]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is externally very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic. Both" authorityName="Pic. Both" box="[784,1086,1378,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[784,963,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bimaculatus</emphasis>
Pic. Both
</taxonomicName>
species can be distinguished from remaining species of the genus on the basis of peculiar dorsal pattern. 
<taxonomicName box="[1050,1227,1419,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1227,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller (TL of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1918" box="[151,326,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipustulatus">
<emphasis box="[151,326,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bipustulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
4.95, TL of 
<taxonomicName box="[474,649,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[474,649,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
3.75), has distinct prehensor, which is indistinct in 
<taxonomicName box="[1251,1429,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuctulatus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1429,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bipuctulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1378,1604]" box="[198,600,1498,1524]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,380,1498,1524]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Redescription.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshitomi, H." box="[387,597,1498,1524]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="295 - 309" refId="ref43358" refString="Yoshitomi, H. (2008) Redescriptions of the type material of eight scirtid species (Insecta, Coleoptera) in the Hope Entomological Collections in Oxford. Japanese Journal of systematic Entomology, 14 (2), 295 - 309." type="journal article" year="2008">Yoshitomi (2008)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1378,1604]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,264,1538,1564]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Note.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, C. G." box="[272,481,1538,1564]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="256 - 273" refId="ref43039" refString="Champion, C. G. (1918) New and little-known saltatorial Dascillidae. Entomological Monthly Magazine, 54, 93 - 103, 139 - 149, 188 - 198, 219 - 225, 256 - 273." type="journal article" year="1918">Champion (1918)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned in the original description that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1918" box="[985,1161,1539,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipustulatus">
<emphasis box="[985,1161,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bipustulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic. A" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. binotatus</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
, but the later species has distinctly larger elytral maculae.
</paragraph>
